The paper deals with private information retrieval (PIR) from decentralized uncoded caching databases, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and distributed systems (cs.DS). The problem also has security implications, which falls under the category of cryptography (cs.CR). The caching and retrieval phases involve decentralized communication (cs.DC) and the optimization of download cost, which can be seen as a resource allocation problem (cs.SI).
